      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@\n+This release improves the accuracy of the `/changelog:add` command documentation by using correct terminology and clarifying configuration file locations.\n+\n+## \ud83d\udc1e Bug fixes\n+\n+### More accurate terminology in changelog add command\n+\n+The `/changelog:add` command documentation now uses the correct terminology \"invoked\" instead of \"loaded\" when referring to skills, and clarifies that the `modules:` configuration is found in the project's `changelog/config.yaml` rather than vaguely referring to \"parent `config.yaml`\". This makes the instructions more accurate and easier to follow.\n+\n+*By @mavam and @claude.*"
